---
const title = "Jamestown: The Best English Colony";
import Header from '../components/header.astro';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>{title}</title>
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 2rem auto;
        padding: 0 1rem;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: #222;
        background: #f9f9f9;
      }
      header.page-header {
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
      }
      h1 {
        font-size: 2.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
        color: #4a2c0a;
      }
      h2 {
        color: #7b5e1e;
        margin-top: 2rem;
      }
      p {
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
      }
      .highlight {
        background-color: #ffeeba;
        padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
        border-radius: 4px;
        font-weight: 600;
      }
      footer {
        margin-top: 3rem;
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        color: #555;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />

    <header class="page-header">
      <h1>Jamestown: The Best English Colony</h1>
      <p><em>Established in 1607, Jamestown laid the foundation for modern America.</em></p>
    </header>

    <section>
      <h2>Historical Significance</h2>
      <p>
        Jamestown was the <span class="highlight">first permanent English settlement</span> in North America,
        setting the stage for English culture and governance on the continent.
      </p>
      <p>
        It survived initial hardships like starvation and conflict, thanks to the resilience and adaptability of its settlers.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Economic Innovation</h2>
      <p>
        Jamestown pioneered the cultivation of <span class="highlight">tobacco as a cash crop</span>, which
        became an economic cornerstone for the colony and later the Southern colonies.
      </p>
      <p>
        The introduction of the Headright System also encouraged immigration and growth.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Political Legacy</h2>
      <p>
        Jamestown established the <span class="highlight">House of Burgesses</span> in 1619,
        the first representative legislative assembly in the Americas,
        which laid the groundwork for American democracy.
      </p>
    </section>

